node.text:
👶As time goes by, your baby will become acquire more and more mobility, and everything that surrounds them will be a new world to explore. ✨Therefore, taking safety measures at home will become your new priority. This is a simple but very useful tip that will keep your little one safe.🙂

#babysafety  #kidssafety  #newparent #newdads #newmommy #preparingforbaby #parentingworkshops #newparent #kidsafety #lifewithtoddlers #childsafety #preventchildinjury #childproofing #babyproofing #preparingforbaby #newbornsafety  #toddlersafety

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by kinedu on September 02, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'Nursery safety tip (A common nursery trend that can be potentially hazardous) ikinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 02, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'Avoid: Placing heavy items above a baby's crib that could fall. Wall- mounted items can come loose if installed improperly. lkinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Instead: Opt for wall decals or murals. This removes all risk from the situation and remains stylish while keeping your baby safe! kinedu'.
Photo by kinedu on September 01, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'Baby proofing checklist around the house Living space Stairs & falls Bathroom Kitchen kinedu'.

node.text:
As babies grow, they also grow more curious! 👶✨ That's why babyproofing your house is so important.

🥳In honor of Baby Safety Month, we've put together a Baby Proofing Checklist to help you out! Want more information? 👆Check out our baby safety classes, download our app and start your 7-day free trial! #linkinbio 

#babyproofing #babyproofingtime #babysafety #fisttimemom #tipsforparents #beingadad  #beingamom

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by kinedu on September 01, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'Baby proofing checklist around the house Living space Stairs & falls Bathroom Kitchen kinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Living Space Anchor furniture that can topple to the wall Remove tablecloths Move unstable floor lamps behind furniture Cover sharp corners and edges Restrict access to fireplaces and stoves Move breakable object out of reach Place cords on blinds and curtains out of reach Cover electrical outlets Reroute or remove dandling electric cords Install pinch guards on doors lkinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stairs & Falls Install baby gates at the top and bottom stairs Move furniture away from deck and balcony railings Cover stair/desk/balcony railings that are more than 3x3.5" apart Put non-slip pads under all rugs Install window guard on accessible windows Restrict access to exercise equipment such as treadmills ikinedu'.
Photo by kinedu on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bathroom Install toilet lock Turn hot water heater down to 120F Add soft cover bathtub faucet lkinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Kitchen ocks Install drawer cabinet, and chest Cover or lock stove and oven controls that are within reach Turn pot/panhandles away from the front of the stove Lock refrigerator and freezer doors ikinedu'.

Photo by kinedu on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A Good Mom days Has bad days great days normal days + overwhelming perfect days + trying days super mom days a whole lot of love + real crazy motherhood days. ikinedu'.

🌟 How exactly do routines help our children and why are they so helpful for them?

1) They foster the development of self-control ☺️
Knowing what comes next gives children security and emotional stability, making them feel more in control.

2) They promote positive behavior
Routines are like a set of steps that guide children towards certain goals 🤩
This can help to ensure children’s safety and help them learn responsible behaviors.

3) They help develop social skills 🤗
Little by little, children start to learn the patterns of social relations and the things that play an important role in them, like sharing, taking turns, and cooperating.

4) They provide learning opportunities 🤓
While adults might find routines boring sometimes, for children, everyday routines are great and fun learning tools. Tell your little one a story about their day! This will help them be aware of their experiences and feelings, making sense of the events in their life.

💙 If you want to learn more about routines and how to use them to stimulate your child’s development, check out kinedu | learn in our Link in Bio!

🌟Yes, of course, there is an ideal time to put babies to bed, since schedules and routines are an important part of the development of a new child!

💤But remember that during the first two months of life, babies do not produce melatonin (the sleep hormone) for this reason it is difficult for them to distinguish between day and night. As these first months go by and the baby acquires melatonin, you will notice that your little one will need to go to bed earlier, which will help them to acquire clearer routines.

* Remember that this is only a recommendation and your baby's bedtime will also depend on the number and duration of naps she has taken during the day.
